revisions.description: The private MIB file includes the DHCPv4 server and relay profile.

hpnicfDhcpServer2Enabled.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2Enabled
hpnicfDhcpServer2Enabled.description: If the value of this object is 'true', the DHCP service is enabled.

hpnicfDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast
hpnicfDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server always uses broadcast to reply the client.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp
hpnicfDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server ignores BOOTP requests.

hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048
hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server use RFC 1048 format to reply to BOOTP requests.

hpnicfDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled
hpnicfDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server handles DHCP option 82.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PingNumber.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PingNumber
hpnicfDhcpServer2PingNumber.description: The number of ping packets sent out.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PingTimeout.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PingTimeout
hpnicfDhcpServer2PingTimeout.description: The delay for the reply of a ping packet in milliseconds.

hpnicfDhcpServer2BadNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2BadNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2BadNum.description: The total number of the bad packets received.

hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREQUEST packets received.

hpnicfDhcpServer2DiscoverNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2DiscoverNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2DiscoverNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDISCOVER packets received from the DHCP clients.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RequestNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RequestNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2RequestNum.description: The total number of the DHCPREQUEST packets received from the DHCP clients.

hpnicfDhcpServer2DeclineNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2DeclineNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2DeclineNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDECLINE packets received from the DHCP clients.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ReleaseNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ReleaseNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2ReleaseNum.description: The total number of the DHCPRELEASE packets received from the DHCP clients.

hpnicfDhcpServer2InformNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2InformNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2InformNum.description: The total number of the DHCPINFORM packets received from the DHCP clients.

hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREPLY packets sent by the DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OfferNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OfferNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2OfferNum.description: The total number of the DHCPOFFER packets sent by the DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2AckNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2AckNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2AckNum.description: The total number of the DHCPACK packets sent by the DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2NakNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2NakNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2NakNum.description: The total number of the DHCPNAK packets sent by the DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage
hpnicfDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage.description: The percentage of IP addresses in use of all DHCP server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNumber.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNumber
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNumber.description: The total number of DHCP server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictNum.description: The total number of conflict IP in all DHCP server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2AutoBindNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2AutoBindNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2AutoBindNum.description: The total number of auto binding IP in DHCP server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ManualBindNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ManualBindNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2ManualBindNum.description: The total number of manual binding IP in DHCP server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum
hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum.description: The total number of expired binding IP in DHCP server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTable.description: A table containing DHCP server pool configurations.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolEntry.description: An entry containing DHCP server pool configurations.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolName.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolName
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolName.description: DHCP server pool name. Once this object is created, the value of this object cannot be modified.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVpnName.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVpnName
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVpnName.description: Name of the VPN instance that the DHCP pool binds to. The value of a zero-length string means the public network. Once this object is created, the value of this object cannot be modified.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetwork.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetwork
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetwork.description: Network address of the primary subnet in a DHCP pool. If the value of this object is set to 0.0.0.0, hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask is set with 0.0.0.0 automatically.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask.description: Network mask of the primary subnet in a DHCP pool. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr.description: Start IP of an address range of the DHCP pool. If the value of this object is set to 0.0.0.0, hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr is set with 0.0.0.0 automatically. Otherwise hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr must be set with an IP address NOT smaller than the value of this object.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr.description: End IP of an address range of the DHCP pool, The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay.description: Number of days of the lease. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour, hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute, hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond together, and any SET operation alone to any of these objects will be regarded as an invalid operation. These objects cannot be set with 0 simultaneously.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour.description: Number of hours of the lease.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond.description: Number of seconds of the lease.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit.description: A flag denoting whether the lease time of a DHCP pool is unlimited.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime.description: The lease time of a DHCP pool in number of timeticks. The value of this object cannot be set to 0 and must be set to 4294967295 or a multiple of 100. If the object is set with 4294967295, the lease time of a DHCP pool is unlimited.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolDomainName.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolDomainName
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolDomainName.description: Domain name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the domain name is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP.description: Gateway IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 gateway addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the gateway address is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP.description: DNS server IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 DNS server addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the DNS address is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP.description: The primary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP.description: The secondary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP clients.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP.description: NetBios server IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 NetBios server addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the NBNS address is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName.description: Boot file name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the boot file name is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP.description: BIMS server IP address. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort is set with 0 and hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort and hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr must be set at the same time while hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr must be set with a non-zero length string.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort.description: BIMS server port number. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP and hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr.description: BIMS server key string. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP and hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNextServer.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNextServer
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolNextServer.description: Next DHCP server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of the next server address is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName.description: TFTP server domain name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the TFTP domain name is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP.description: TFTP server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of the TFTP server address is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP.description: Voice backup server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of voice backup server IP address is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP.description: Voice failover IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr must be set with a non-zero length string at the same time.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr.description: Voice failover dialer string for DHCP clients. The characters in the string must be '0' ~ '9',or '*'. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP.description: Voice network calling processing IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of voice network calling processing IP address is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId.description: Voice VLAN ID for DHCP clients. If the value of this object is set to 65535, hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl is set with 'false' automatically. Otherwise hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl.description: Enable status of the specified voice VLAN for DHCP clients. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass.description: Enable the user class verification. When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server processes packets from DHCP clients in the defined user classes. The user class verification does not apply to packets from DHCP clients with static bindings.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable.description: A table for applying a DHCP pool on interfaces.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry.description: An entry for applying a DHCP pool on the interface.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName
hpnicfDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName.description: The name of the DHCP pool that apply to the interface. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration will be deleted.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable.description: A table containing the secondary network configuration of DHCP pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the secondary network for DHCP pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNw.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNw
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNw.description: Network address of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask.description: Network mask of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP.description: Gateway IP addresses of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 gateway addresses can be configured for a secondary network, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the gateway address is removed.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassTable.description: A table containing address range of the DHCP server pool for user classes.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry.description: An entry containing address range of DHCP pools for user classes.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStart
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.description: Start address of an address range for a DHCP user class. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd.description: End address of an address range for a DHCP user class. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStart together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. This object must be set with an IP address NOT smaller than the value of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassStart and hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable.description: A table containing the static binding configurations in DHCP pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the static binding in DHCP pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP.description: Ip address of a static binding in a DHCP pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask.description: Network mask of a static binding in a DHCP pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID.description: Client identifier of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType.description: Hardware type of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. 'default' indicates that the hardware type is unknown. If the value of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID is set to a non-zero length string, the object is set with 'default' automatically. Otherwise it cannot be set with 'default'. 'ethernet' indicates that the hardware type is ethernet. If the value of hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr is set with a non-zero length string, the default value of this object is 'ethernet'. 'tokenRing' indicates that the hardware type is token-ring.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID or (hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHardAddr and hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolStaticHardType) must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable.description: A table for configuring user-defined options for DHCP pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring user-defined options for DHCP pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptType.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptType
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptType.description: Option type. 'ascii' means using the ascii string that is defined by hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii to fill in the option. 'hex' means using the hex string that is defined by hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr to fill in the option. 'ip' means using the IP string that is defined by hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr to fill in the option.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii.description: Ascii string of an option. If hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'ascii', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even. If hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'hex', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr.description: IP string of an option. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. 1 to 8 IP addresses can be configured simultaneously. If hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'ip', this object must be set with a non-zero length string that must contain at least one IP address.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolOptType must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable.description: A table for configuring forbidden IP for a DHCP server pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry.description: An entry for configuring forbidden IP for a DHCP server pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP.description: Forbidden IP of the DHCP pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassTable.description: A table for configuring user class to DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassEntry.description: An entry for configuring user class to DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleTable.description: A table for configuring option rules used to match DHCP users.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleEntry.description: An entry for configuring option rules used to match DHCP users.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptMask.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptMask
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptMask.description: The mask used to match options. The length of this object must be same with that of hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.description: The option offset used to match users. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr, hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptLength
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.description: The option length used to match user options. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleOptCode must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidTable.description: A table for configuring forbidden IP range to DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidEntry.description: An entry for configuring forbidden IP range to DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName
hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName.description: Name of the VPN instance that the forbidden IP range binds to. If the value of this object is 0x1, the network that the forbidden IP range belongs to is the public network.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidStart.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidStart
hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidStart.description: Start IP of forbidden IP range.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidEnd.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidEnd
hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidEnd.description: End IP of forbidden IP range.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2ForbidRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeTable.description: A table for displaying free IP range for DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeEntry.description: An entry for displaying free IP range for DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeStart.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeStart
hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeStart.description: Start IP of free IP range.

hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeEnd.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeEnd
hpnicfDhcpServer2FreeEnd.description: End IP of free IP range.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictTable.description: A table for displaying the information of conflict IP for DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictEntry.description: An entry for displaying the information of conflict IP for DHCP server.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictType.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictType
hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictType.description: Type of the detection of conflict IP. 'detectByServer' denotes that the conflict is detected by DHCP server. 'detectByClient' denotes that the conflict is detected by DHCP client.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictTime.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictTime
hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictTime.description: Time when the conflict is detected. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredTable.description: A table for displaying the information of expired IP for DHCP Server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry.description: An entry of objects for displaying information of expired IP for DHCP server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredTime.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredTime
hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredTime.description: Expired time. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseTable.description: A table for displaying the information of IP in use for DHCP Server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry.description: An entry of objects for displaying information of IP in use for DHCP server pools.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId
hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId.description: User's VLAN ID. 65535 means that a client doesn't have VLAN ID or have an invalid VLAN ID.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease
hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease.description: End time of lease. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex
hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex.description: Interface index information. If the value of this object is zero, the interface is unknown.

hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable.description: A table containing option group of the DHCP server pool for user classes.

hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry.description: An entry containing option group of DHCP pools for user classes.

hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hpnicfDhcpServer2DefOptGrpId must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassTable.description: A table containing valid user classes for DHCP server pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry.description: An entry containing valid user classes for DHCP server pool.

hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable.description: A table for configuring hardware address rules used to match DHCP users.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry.description: An entry for configuring hardware address rules used to match DHCP users.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress.description: Hardware address for a rule. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask.description: Mask of hardware address for a rule. The structure of the OCTET STRING is the same with hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType.description: Hardware type for a rule. The codes of all hardware types see ARP section in RFC 1700. The SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrAddress and hpnicfDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server option groups.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting an option group.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionTable.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionTable
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionTable.description: A table for configuring options in an option group.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionEntry
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionEntry.description: An entry containing objects for configuring an option in an option group.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionType.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionType
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionType.description: Option type. 'ascii' means using the ascii string that is defined by hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionAscii to fill in the option. 'hex' means using the hex string that is defined by hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionHexStr to fill in the option. 'ip' means using the IP string that is defined by hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionIPStr to fill in the option.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionAscii.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionAscii
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionAscii.description: Ascii string of an option. If hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'ascii', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionHexStr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionHexStr
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even. If hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'hex', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionIPStr.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionIPStr
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionIPStr.description: IP string of an option. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. 1 to 8 IP addresses can be configured simultaneously. If hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'ip', this object must be set with a non-zero length string that must contain at least one IP address.

hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hpnicfDhcpServer2OptionType must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord
hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord.description: If the value is 'true', user information will be recorded.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh
hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh.description: If the value is 'true', user information will be refreshed on timer.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime
hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime.description: User information refresh interval in seconds. If the value of the object is set to 0, the interval is calculated automatically by the number of user information entries.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr
hpnicfDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr.description: User address to be released. The structure of the OCTET STRING is IP address:VPN name. If the VPN instance name is NOT specified, the IP address is in public network.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2RxClientNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2RxClientNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2RxClientNum.description: The total number of the packets received from DHCP clients by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2TxClientNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2TxClientNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2TxClientNum.description: The total number of the packets transmitted to DHCP clients by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2RxServerNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2RxServerNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2RxServerNum.description: The total number of the packets received from DHCP Servers by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2TxServerNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2TxServerNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2TxServerNum.description: The total number of the packets transmitted to DHCP Servers by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2BadNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2BadNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2BadNum.description: The total number of the bad packets received.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREQUEST packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDISCOVER packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2RequestNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2RequestNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2RequestNum.description: The total number of the DHCPREQUEST packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2DeclineNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2DeclineNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2DeclineNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDECLINE packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum.description: The total number of the DHCPRELEASE packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2InformNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2InformNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2InformNum.description: The total number of the DHCPINFORM packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREPLY packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2OfferNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2OfferNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2OfferNum.description: The total number of the DHCPOFFER packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2AckNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2AckNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2AckNum.description: The total number of the DHCPACK packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2NakNum.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2NakNum
hpnicfDhcpRelay2NakNum.description: The total number of the DHCPNAK packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable.description: A table for configuring relay functions for interfaces.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry.description: An entry for configuring relay functions for an interface.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay.description: If the value is 'true', the DHCP relay function would be enabled on this interface.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac.description: If the value is 'true', the function of checking MAC address of packets received from the interface would be enabled.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable.description: If DHCP relay supports option 82 functions, the value is 'true'. If DHCP relay does NOT support option 82 functions, the value is 'false'.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy.description: The strategies of DHCP relay handling option 82. 'drop' indicates DHCP relay discarding the request packet including option 82. 'keep' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet without any change of the option 82. 'replace' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet on condition that it generates a new option 82 to replace the original one.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.description: The mode of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'normal' is the standard mode. 'verbose' is the detailed mode. 'userDefine' is the user-defined mode. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.description: Type of access node identifier that is used to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82 when the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is set to 'verbose'. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode. 'invalid' indicates that the node identifier is NOT used to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'verbose', the value of this object is set to 'invalid' automatically. Otherwise the value of this object cannot be set to 'invalid'. 'mac' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the MAC of DHCP relay input interface. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is set to 'verbose', the default value of this object is 'mac'. 'sysname' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the sysname of the DHCP relay device. 'userDefine' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the string defined by the object of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr. If the value is set to 'userDefine', the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr must be set to a non-zero length string simultaneously.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the node identifier in the verbose mode. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'verbose', or the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType is NOT 'userDefine', it is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode and hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82 in the user-define mode. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', it is set to a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat.description: The format of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'hex' is the hex format. 'ascii' is the ascii format. 'undefine' is the undefine format. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'normal', the value of this object is set to 'hex' automatically and cannot be set to 'undefine'. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'verbose', the default value of this object is 'undefine'. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'userDefine', the value of this object is set to 'ascii' automatically and cannot be set to other value. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.description: The mode of the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'normal' is the standard mode. 'sysname' is the sysname mode. 'userDefine' is the user-defined mode. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the remote ID in the user-defined mode. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', it is set to a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat
hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat.description: The format of the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'hex' is the hex format. 'ascii' is the ascii format. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is 'sysname' or 'userDefine', this object is set with 'ascii' automatically and cannot be set with other value. If the value of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is 'normal', the default value of this object is 'hex'. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable
hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable.description: A table for configuring a DHCP server address on the interface.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry
hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry.description: An entry for configuring a DHCP server address on the interface.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable
hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable.description: A table containing the user information of DHCP client.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry
hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry.description: An entry containing the user information of DHCP client.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex
hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex.description: VPN index of the DHCP client.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex
hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex.description: The index of the interface that DHCP client adhered to. 0 means that no interface information is recorded in the user information entry.

hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Only destroy action is allow to use.
